Tried coming here for lunch today and at noon, it was totally dead. Only saw one employee in the whole place, who promptly disappeared after instructing us to sit wherever we wanted. Not a single other customer was there, and there was no sushi chef behind the bar or anything. They also didn't have any lunch specials. Everything was full price. Maybe that's why no customers were there?  While waiting for someone to show up and take our order, we noticed that the paper menu on our table was wrinkled and filthy. Upon further inspection of our table, we realized that the platters and soy sauce bowls in front of all three of us were dirty. I picked up the bowl in front of me and scraped off various different bits of dried on food, and so did my companions.  We got up and walked out. A place that serves raw fish should have very high standards of cleanliness, and Moira appeared to be woefully lacking in that regard. Very disappointing.

